
Control Logic Inputs:

  [12]    - unused
  [4:11]  - Instruction
  [3]     - Flag (zero-flag if lsb=0, carry-flag if lsb=1)
  [0:2]   - Step

Control Logic Outputs:

  [12:15] - Data Bus Driver
            0 → r1
            1 → r2
            2 → r3
            3 → r4
            4 → ram
            5 → ah
            6 → al
            7 → add
            8 → add-c
            9 → sub
            a → sub-c
            b → or
            c → and
            d → xor
            e → CFG
            f → I/O

  [8:11]  - Data Bus Consumer
            0 → r1
            1 → r2
            2 → r3
            3 → r4
            4 → ram
            5 → dh
            6 → dl
            7 → a1
            8 → a2
            9 → IR
            a → none
            b → none
            c → none
            d → none
            e → CFG
            f → I/O

  [6:7]   - Address Bus Driver
            0 → PC
            1 → DC
            2 → SP
            3 → DH/DL

  [3:5]   - Address Bus Consumer
            0 → PC
            1 → DC
            2 → SP
            3 → AH/AL
            4 → none
            5 → none
            6 → none
            7 → none

  [0:2]   - Misc
            0 → PC Count
            1 → DC Count
            2 → SP Increase
            3 → SP Decrease
            4 → none (I/O control?)
            5 → none
            6 → none
            7 → Instruction complete

Assembler macros to implement:

        ldi     dc, 0xXXXX
        ldi     sp, 0xXXXX
        halt
        reset
        rom-enable
        rom-disable

Features that may be useful:
        mov     rX, ah/al
        and-cmp rX, rX
        I/O block transfer
        notification-register
        rshift
        invert
        zero-register

Instructions that could be dropped:
        One of add / addc
        One of sub / subc

256 instructions:
 00-1f  (32) : Move and load-immediate
 20-5f  (64) : Memory instructions
 60-6f  (16) : Jump instructions
 70-7f  (16) : I/O instructions
 80-ff (128) : ALU instructions


